observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the City Mayor:
a. form a committee consisting of competent City personnel to conduct further investigation and validation of the reported cases of duplication of payments to 2,015 beneficiaries and the additional 430 cases of duplications of beneficiary’s name, the barangay address, and bank/e-wallet account number to ascertain the existence of duplications in the payment of financial assistance and to recommend measures on how the City could recoup the amount mistakenly received by the beneficiaries listed in Appendices 10 and 11;
b. direct the Officer in charge of the City IT Unit to conduct a thorough assessment of the City’s existing database of households/families and the policies and procedures in the preparation of list of beneficiaries to determine the actual issues that could affect the integrity of the database and generated reports, and to recommend appropriate measures to ensure that the problems encountered in the distribution of the emergency subsidy or "Ayuda" will not be repeated;
c. require the facilitating bank to explain in writing, together with supporting documents, why there are 197 cases involving financial assistance amounting to P1,350,000.00 with the same or duplicate transaction reference number as listed in Appendix 12;
d. direct the City Accountant and the City Treasurer to immediately return to the Bureau of Treasury the unexpended balance of the fund amounting to P8,970,030.00; and
e. require the aforecited personnel or office to prepare and submit the reports on their findings and/or action taken, copy furnished the COA Audit Team, for further evaluation.

We recommended that the City Mayor:
a. direct the City Accountant to adopt the Perpetual Inventory Method in all procurement of supplies and materials by recording the transactions initially as an asset using the appropriate inventory accounts prescribed in the Revised Chart of Accounts for LGUs;
b. require the General Services Officer to prepare the Weekly Summary of Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Fund (LDRRMF) Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) duly supported by RIS for submission to the Accounting Office for proper recording of disbursements.

observations.managementAction:
The City Mayor agreed to undertake the following courses of action as per his letter to the COA Audit Team dated March 21, 2022:
a. to form a committee which will perform further investigation and validation of the reported cases of duplications in the payment of Ayuda and to ascertain their existence, and recommend measures to recover from the beneficiaries the amount mistakenly received by them or in excess of the allowed amount;
b. the City IT Department to conduct thorough assessment of the database of the Ayuda beneficiaries, examine the policies and procedures in the preparation of the list of beneficiaries to determine the actual issues that could affect the integrity of the database and generated reports, and recommend measures to ensure that the problems encountered in the distribution of Ayuda will not be repeated;
c. to write to the facilitating bank to provide explanation on the 197 cases of duplication of transaction reference number in the distribution of Ayuda;
d. the City Accountant and City Treasurer to immediately study and determine the existence of unexpended balance of the fund due to the national government; and
e. the foregoing City Officials to prepare and submit to the COA Audit Team the reports on their findings and/or actions.
Moreover, as per letter dated April 12, 2022, of the Head, City Information Technology and Records Management Unit (CITRMU), a comprehensive and thorough assessment was conducted by their Office and they identified the following issues and concerns:
The existing database of household has duplicate records due to the following:
a. declaration of different head of the family with the same family members;
b. instead of declaration of additional family members itself, names of the entire family members listed in the old forms have been included;
c. names of the family members were misspelled, used maiden name, nicknames, or other aliases;
d. date of birth was not in its correct format; and
e. submission of names to other barangays.
In order to mitigate the effects and prevent the reoccurrence of this, the CITRMU has initiated the following actions:
a) Complete review of the “ayuda” pay-out process: from receiving of forms, encoding of data, uploading to the database, and finally, to the extraction of data from the database and generation of order list of beneficiaries for pay-out.
b) Creation of another system for checking of duplicate pay-outs before sending to the designated payment platform.
c) Creation of another system named “AYUDA SEARCH” to enable the helpdesk to manually verify the ayuda status of a beneficiary. These are: “PAID, NOT PAID OR DUPLICATE PAYMENT”.
d) Creation of a team that is tasked on verifying “dubious” entries from the database in order to check whether it is actually a case of duplication of data or it’s just a case of “close match”.
e) Additional verification step has been added to the process of loading data to the database.

observations.recommendation:
